name: Design Museum
review_text: It saddens me to review it low, but I must agree with other comments. After visiting both museums that came with the ticket purchase… I think the best part was admiring the architecture of the design museum: it’s magnificent. Some of the exhibits were interesting like learning about Finnish designers. However some other exhibits were really really meh that may require a different approach to viewing art. Overall I wouldn’t skip it if there’s time in your day. The price should absolutely be lower.

name: Design Museum
review_text:
Really cute museum. A little more expensive than we’re used to in the UK (where most of our museums are free). They do offer student discounts and don’t seem to check ID.

We went to see the mending exhibition and it was nice.

name: Design Museum
review_text: I had a long layover in Helsinki before my flight, so I decided not to waste time at the airport. After some research, I chose to visit the Design Museum. The adult ticket was €20! I honestly think they realized this museum alone might not justify the price, so they included admission to the Architecture Museum across the street as well. Both museums were interesting, but I agree they are quite small, and I lean toward the opinion that the ticket price isn’t worth it.

name: Design Museum
review_text: Quite a small museum but really interesting to see the Finnish influence on a range of objects and cultural classics. Ticket price is a bit steep (20€) but it does give access to the also small Architecture museum just behind it. Also worth a visit. Be prepared to read a lot in both to get bang for your buck.

name: Design Museum
review_text: Design needs to be useful, and this museum perfectly conveys that message. Located in Helsinki, this Design Museum uniquely demonstrates how to transform ideas and needs into the simplest and most directly useful forms. Here, you can uncover the inherent logic of design.

name: Design Museum
review_text:
Wouldn't really call this a "museum". Some interesting industrial/furniture design in the downstairs area. Almost felt like the upstairs was grasping at straws trying to fill the space.

Glad I went in first and was out in 15mins. Saved my wife the additional 20€. Not worth it.

name: Design Museum
review_text:
Should I was able, I would have given a 0 star...I am very disappointed by this museum and even more by the Finnish architecture museum.Not worth a euro to be spent on a ticket visit !
Keep your money for Helsinki Art Museum and other great places to visit in this stunning capital and other places in Finland (Suomi).

name: Design Museum
review_text: I was most interested in seeing Finnish distinctive designs, sustainable designs, historical design breakthroughs, and unique features of some collectible designs. However, many of the designs' notable characteristics weren't described; instead, they wrote about secondary information. There was also a wall explaining the design process, which I wouldn't be interested in without specific examples, as this process can be understood from general design books. Overall, it was still quite interesting. If you have the Helsinki Card, it's worth a visit. As someone not from a European country, I found the 20 euro admission quite expensive for the exhibition content. Although it did save me a lot of time compared to researching on my own...

name: Design Museum
review_text:
A shame. It's shocking that for a country with such strong design traditions the museum is so bad. Small, chaotic expositions without any meaningful information just a bit of social commentary not relevant to the objects. Only part about Alto's famous vase was interesting, the rest is awful. Strongly advised not to waste time on that. Literally 4 cases in Emil Altonen museum in Tampere had more info about Finnish design than all of that.
Joint Architecture Museum is also terrible. The architecture-related permanent exhibition is not that bad (adding social/historical background to arxhitecture is important and interesting!) but it's small, old and in general the level of free exhibition in tourist information center, not 20€ museum. The current temporary exibition is a sad, ugly joke. It claims to be about fixing (mending) and cleaning. You can see there such amazing exhibits as rubber gloves and mops/brooms. Literal cleaning supplies because apparently people running this circus are so removed from reality those thing are unusual and interesting for them.
It's beyond me why this is allowed. There are such strong design traditions in Finland. Such great architects. Helsinki alone are a marvel. And this is what we're getting. Shame. Shame, shame, shame.

name: Design Museum
review_text: I regret to say that this museum, along with the added architecture museum across the street including the temp. exhibitions ‘FIX & Repair’ falls short in showcasing the rich legacy of Finnish design and architecture, which is renowned. The exhibits lack creativity and engaging content, with only one room offering anything noteworthy. Overall, it's a missed opportunity and not worth the admission fee. A more thoughtful and dynamic presentation would do more justice to Finish design.

name: Design Museum
review_text: To be honest, I found this to be a real let down. With Finland being k own for its design, I expected a lot more. To go through both buildings didn’t take long at all, especially the architecture part.

name: Design Museum
review_text:
Out of the 4 exhibit in the two buildings of the museum, only 2 were actually interesting and about design. One exhibit was about cleaning supplies and you could have “fun” with them. Maybe I just don’t understand art.
I found the entrance price too expensive for what you get.

name: Design Museum
review_text:
A historical brief about Finnish design in two-storey historical building.

It was a dissapointment for me as it is very small and weak museum. Also, entrance fee of 20€ is a high pricing for this kind of museum. It is better to keep your expectations low.

It is possible to visit the the rest of the exhibition in Museum of Fınnish Architecture with the same ticket in the same day.

name: Design Museum
review_text: I don’t know why this museum has such low/mediocre reviews! I think if you have an appreciation for design, it’s a great experience. Yes, the ticket price is high and it’s a small museum, but the content is lovely and there is a lot to learn. I do wish there were more details or write ups about the work on the didactics but regardless, I enjoyed my visit and would recommend the museum on a trip to Helsinki!

name: Design Museum
review_text: There were some interesting exhibits but this was somewhat uninspiring for a design museum. Even worse was the adjacent Architecture Museum, which you can enter with the same ticket.

name: Design Museum
review_text: Quite strange museum, unusual for me. But we're interesting to visit.

name: Design Museum
review_text: Well, this is very well done! It will show you the most important and iconic designers, products and thoughts in Finnish history of design. I really like how they apply equity and inclusion as a part of the presentation of the design. I would appreciate more engaging elements and more accessible materials for different needs. Otherwise it was nice experience.
owner_answer: Glad to hear you enjoyed your visit and thank you for the feedback!

name: Design Museum
review_text:
I enjoyed my visit, but it becomes quickly clear that the museum is moving to a new location.

The ticket allows you to visit both museums, the design and the museum of architecture, which is located behind it. The exhibitions feel dated and waiting for a refresh. The museum of  architecture gives interesting information about how society changed during the decades, but stops in 1970.... There have been a few decades since.

The design museum had some interesting objects, I didn't know that the scissors have been improved in design by a Finn for example, other than that, I breezed through the other exhibitions as they were not as interesting.

Until the refresh, skip if you have limited time in Helsinki.

name: Design Museum
review_text:
We had recently been to the Danish Design museum in Copenhagen which is one of the best museums we have ever been to and incidentally was cheaper than this museum. They couldn’t be more different.

I suggest whoever runs this museum (and the architecture museum next door which honestly calling it a museum is being charitable, it’s more a student art installation of 2 rooms) should go and visit the Danish design museum in Copenhagen.

Beyond the industrial design area downstairs, which is quite interesting, the upstairs is very lacklustre and as others have mentioned felt like they were desperate to fill the empty space. All the rich history of Finnish design and it was a missed opportunity. You will learn more about Finnish architecture by walking the streets around the museum so save your money!

Cannot recommend this. There’s plenty of small museums we’ve been to on our travels that do a lot with limited space or resources, but this is not it. We walked out thinking hey at least we’ve now got a new bar for worst museum, but the fact it’s 20 euro per person actually makes it feel a bit of a scam.

name: Design Museum
review_text: The Design museum of Helsinki has always something worthwhile to show and is a must for those interested in design. Finnish design and architecture. The museum has also a fabulous cafe that offers its well-known liquorice buns for those who want something sweet with the coffee.

name: Design Museum
review_text:
I would give this place one star if I could, but it wasn't that bad. I've been to plenty of design/contemporary art museums, and they were all better than this. Not sure if this is due to their transitional period waiting to move to their new building (with the neighboring Architecture Museum - which was also terrible), or too heavy a focus on the joint exhibition.

None of the exhibitions were that eye-catching, and I knew that it was not a great experience when I saw design exhibitions both in Oslo and Copenhagen later on the trip which both beat this one by leagues. Their cafe and the beautiful neighborhood streets nearby are the only redeeming factors!

name: Design Museum
review_text: Wonderful museum with three floors. When we visited there were two temporary exhibitions - top floor there were tapestries by Kustaa Saksi. These were quite eerie and otherworldly. On the basement floor there was a light exhibit by graphic designer of the year Tomi Leppänen which was beautiful. The ground floor had the permanent exhibit with Finnish design icons. There is a café and gift shop with some nice bits and pieces.
owner_answer: Thank you for your review and lovely feedback!

name: Design Museum
review_text: An extremely disappointing experience. First floor and second floor filled with very random exhibits showcasing Finnish industrial design. On top of that, the toilets are under renovation (and the working ones in less than perfect condition). Ticket for an adult 20 euros. All in all: it's better to walk around the city.

name: Design Museum
review_text:
The regular exhibition is nice! U can see Finnish classics like Fiskars and metro seats.
The exhibitions that change are always awesome!
Place has cafe and is at great location with easy accessibility. Beautiful building also.

name: Design Museum
review_text: Very disappointing visit to the Design and Architecture Museums. Really not worth €20 admission. We saw better design in shop windows and better architecture around the city. The Design Museum devoted much space to meaningless exhibits reflecting on what it means to run a design museum instead of the actual design, most of which was in any case trivial. The Architecture Museum devoted one entire floor to the cleaning of the museum! Better to visit real.architecture and design at Oodi and the Church in the Rock.

name: Design Museum
review_text: Pretty cool, not the biggest museum out there. It has a big focus on glassware and glass art on the second floor. The first floor has an exhibition with more broad design topics, like fashion and furniture which is interesting!
owner_answer: Thank you for leaving a review! We hope you come again!

name: Design Museum
review_text:
Tiny museum, has 3 very different exhibition
One floor is full of tapestry
Other one is modern art (light work) few fun things, but nothing too fascinating
Last floor is permanent exhibition with some old & older items
owner_answer: Thank you for your review, and added photos!

name: Design Museum
review_text: Our visit was disappointing.  We expected to see more about Finnish design related to furniture and clothing but the biggest display was on Fiskar.  Also while there was information about Angry Birds and how it was influential in the development of the video industry, the 2 screens that were supposed to present the game were not working.

name: Design Museum
review_text: All in all, it is a nice museum and it provides interesting information! Unfortunately, many things were under maintenance or closed due to Covid. Furthermore, half of the exhibition is about Fashion which is quite a lot.
owner_answer: Thank you for visiting and leaving feedback, Laura!

name: Design Museum
review_text: Engaging and carefully considered exhibits, with themes relevant to tourists and locals alike. Well worth a visit for design inspiration, stories from Finland’s past and hope for the future. Also stop for coffee or a meal at Taito!
owner_answer: Thank you for visiting and for the review as well!

name: Design Museum
review_text: Pleasant, intimate design museum in central Helsinki. The Finnish design exhibits are well done and thoughtful, tho small. When I visited there was an excellent exhibit on Josef Frank that took up half the museum. The cafe is nice, too. Small gift shop.

name: Design Museum
review_text: Very nice museum for those who show interest into design and architecture.  Loads of models and drawings, traditional Finnish patterns and objects along with iconic designs (chairs, phones and other furniture). It should be on the 'to see' list!

name: Design Museum
review_text: Hi! It is nice to visit the design museum. Classic things and objects are hanging on the walls. Vr glasses experience is fantastic. A very well  combination of old and new culture. If you visit the design 🖼️ musium, I hope you will enjoy it a lot. Thanks 😊
owner_answer: Glad you liked our exhibition! Thank you!

name: Design Museum
review_text: To open only at 11 am a Museum in the capital of Finland is a shame. Some of the best Finnish artists are better displayed in foreign Museums ( Milan, Triennale; Vitra ,Germany etc).

name: Design Museum
review_text:
Sorry I can’t give a better star rating Designmuseo. Just Is not enough to see, more of a small display than a museum. Really should be free admission.
Perhaps one day Finland, with SO MUCH design and innovation and Architecture should have a designed and Architectural museum building full of what is on offer all over Helsinki
Should be as brilliant as Copenhagen Design Museum.
Has a nice little cafe and shop. All areas are wheelchair accessible via a lift

name: Design Museum
review_text: Well laid out. Describes the origins and concepts inherent in Finnish design and the Inspirations of the designers with clever displays and easy to assimilate language, interesting and engaging even for the casually interested.

name: Design Museum
review_text: I was here two times and every time was amazed how comfortable it is to visit. Everywhere you can find a place to sit, and many objects to interact with. I would highly recommend to visit a museum to get to know about Finnish design and its contribution. However, there some exhibits located on the level of the knee that was quite tricky to explore cause I have to look down too much to read the text about auch exhibits on the corridor. On the photo there are a small park behind the building and and an exhibit made of cute tiles.
owner_answer: Thank you for your review and feedback, great to hear that you visited us twice! Behind the Design Museum (the yard between the Design Museum and Museum of Finnish Architecture) is located Alusta Pavilion. This project explores nature-culture relations and offers a place for encounters between humans and non-human animals in urban space. The pavilion functions as a platform for environmental discourse, both on the level of its form and materiality, and the different activities which take place there. It comprises a pollinator friendly meadow and structures made with clay in its different forms; unfired and fired brick and rammed earth. Alusta is realized by a multidisciplinary group lead by Suomi/Koivisto architects.

name: Design Museum
review_text: Definitely worth a visit while in Helsinki! The collection on display for Utopia of Finish design and I was blown away by it! Go go go!
owner_answer: Thank you for your feedback and review. We are so happy to hear that you enjoyed!

name: Design Museum
review_text: Really wonderful museum to see some history and examples of creative Finnish design. Really enjoyed the temporary art exhibit as well!

name: Design Museum
review_text: Amazing museum that can always guarantee an eye opening experience with every exhibition. The museum itself is a bit small although there are 3 levels. Sometimes I feel there is not enough space between the art pieces. Nonetheless, the exhibitions are usually thoughtful and creative. The permanent exhibition on the first floor gives an overview of the Finnish design which focuses on practicality and simplicity. Some of the items are classic so don’t be surprised that many of them can still easily be found in the shop or regular households like Marimekko shirts and Fiskar scissors.

name: Design Museum
review_text: This was the best museum I have ever been to.  Every exhibit was informative, well thought out, and breathtaking.  I came in 2019 when they had their "Secret Universe" exhibit and was absolutely blown away.  Had a wonderful time here.
owner_answer: We are happy to hear that you had a good time! Thank you for the review!

name: Design Museum
review_text: The design museum is big and there are many different sections. It is nice place to visit if your are bored of visiting other museums in a city. The entrance is free if you have Helsinki card with you. Its takes maximum 1.30-2 hrs to see the museum. Time to time there are different design related workshops for kids. The best section is to see the gaming section where you see how they were created. The glass and wooden section is also quite good. Must see if you have Helsinki card and if you are into product design.

name: Design Museum
review_text: Small but very interesting museum that touches on many different aspects and types of design.

name: Design Museum
review_text: Good exhibition of Finnish glass design. Glass seems to be a thing for Finnish design. Some similarities seem to repeat from exhibition to another but lots of new things still so it remains worth visiting over and over again.

name: Design Museum
review_text: Very nice collection. Perhaps a bit smaller than I would have expected taking into consideration the amount of important designers in the country. I’m an interior designer and enjoyed seeing the iconic pieces.
owner_answer: Thank you for visiting and for your input!

name: Design Museum
review_text: Do the construction going on? I gave it one star less than I would normally give it after the construction's finished and the other exhibits open up. This will be a really good museum

name: Design Museum
review_text:
Way overpriced, 15 euros is too much imo. The design television was the highlight for me…
Spend max 1 hour but we’ve been there for about 45 minutes

name: Design Museum
review_text:
Pros: Walking distance from the central railway station, located in the charming building close to the beautiful church. The museum offers an efficient intro to the famous Finnish brands.
Cons: the exhibitions of the Finnish brands must be enlarge; some well-known in Finland and abroad Finnish brands are totally missing; keep un update with the latest products and solutions; there are some products and solurions which have nothing to do with Finland

name: Design Museum
review_text: An interesting experience in Finnish design. A couple floors of exhibits showing off the history, with only a few points non functioning. The large carpet installation was a particular highlight of the upper floor, great tactile experience to walk around on. In terms of price, I think its worth it if you're using the Helsinki card to see multiple museums in a day. Your mileage may vary depending on your feelings about design.

name: Design Museum
review_text: An excellent museum to know about Finnish design. You would find things you might not even know before they were from Finland .

name: Design Museum
review_text: Favorite museum I believe in Helsinki. Unfortunately, the 2nd floor was closed but got in at a discounted rate.  It was absolutely beautiful!
owner_answer: We are glad to hear that! Our new main exhibition about fresh Finnish fashion design, "Intimacy" just opened on the 2nd floor and it continues the theme of being absolutely beautiful!

name: Design Museum
review_text:
The museum to visit in Helsinki.
Displys in three floors, healthy and plentiful food at the restaurant well matches the designshops selections in design delicasies.
owner_answer: Thank you for the great review, Ville! We're glad that you enjoyed your visit!

name: Design Museum
review_text:
A very good museum. Design is so much important. Always design so it is
Useful
Serves its purpose
Safe
Looks Good

name: Design Museum
review_text: Went on a Sunday to visit the Secret Universe exhibition by Aamu Song and Johan Olin and loved how fun,  quirky and beautiful the installations were. A very good reminder of the skill that goes into good and traditional craftsmanship. An eye opening exhibition if you want to further develop an appreciation for the effort and skill it takes to not only make and preserve these traditions but to also collaborate across traditions, cultures and fields like the design world and the worlds of the "masters". Left me a lasting impression.

name: Design Museum
review_text: The exhibition of the joint work the couple Nurmesniemi was the best use you could give the relatively small space. The nice thing was that you could have se some of the items exhibited. Really inspiring!

name: Design Museum
review_text:
Design museum in Helsinki is a great place to visit if you are interested to know more about Finnish design and designers.The museum welcomes also children. There are instructions, maps and special materials for kids for exploring the museum.
The Design museum is situated in the city centrum, only about one kilometer from the main railway station. So it's a nice stroll there or you can take tram no. 10 that takes you there in 5 minutes. The building itself is a beautiful old building, dated back in 1894 by architect Gustav Nyström. The building served as a school until 1977.
There is a small souvenir shop and a cozy cafe/bar in the museum.
Utopia Now exhibition is the story of Finnish design with familiar names like Aalto, Arabia, Fiskars, Marimekko, Sarpaneva, Iittala, Aarikka and many others.
There are permanent collections and changing exhibitions in the Design museum. Some of the pictures are from the special exhibition of spring 2018 "California: Designing Freedom".

name: Design Museum
review_text: Very unique experience, I gained a lot of new knowledge. There was also a VR headset, which we could use for free!

name: Design Museum
review_text: Smaller than expected, but power-packed. Angry Birds! Nokia! Fiskars! Finland has influence and Finnish design is lovely.
owner_answer: Love to hear that! Thank you for leaving a review!

name: Design Museum
review_text: Really nice museum about design, Finnish design and Scandinavian design. Quite huge collection of items presented in very attractive way. You should also visit the shop and try delicious soup :)

name: Design Museum
review_text: Great museum in the center of Helsinki focused on the history and process of Finnish design. One stationary exhibit highlighting key design elements coming out of the region and two rotating exhibits. Great gift shop as well. Takes about one hour to tour.

name: Design Museum
review_text: This museum attracted me because there are lots of positive feedback on TripAdvisor. But I should confess that it didn’t impress me at all except an exhibition of carpets. There are not so many interesting things to observe or get inspired. Also, there are a shop and a cafe inside of the building which are very cosy and it’s nice to have a short break after the museum.
owner_answer: Thank you for your review and feedback. Lovely to hear that you liked the exhibition Kustaa Saksi: In the Borderlands with jacquard-weaved textiles. And super that you also mentioned our Design Shop and Café :)

name: Design Museum
review_text: The exhibits did a good job highlighting the different areas that Finnish designers have contributed to, but to be honest I was expecting a little more considering Finland's rich history of design. Museum shop had a great selection though.

name: Design Museum
review_text: Wasted my time coming here. The ticket is super expensive and the exhibits are mostly nonsense. This is not a serious/educative/scientific museum at all, it’s more like an assorted collection of everyday items. Just go to any random store and look at the items in the shelves.

name: Design Museum
review_text: Usually when I visit art museums, I stand in front of individual art pieces with my hand on my chin looking really focused, hoping to look like I understand what is going on. At this museum, because everything is segmented very well, I could stand in one corner with my hand on my chin collectively not understanding what is going on.

name: Design Museum
review_text: Expect a small but quality exhibition and you’ll be pleased. This isn’t a sprawling design museum, but its constraints allow it to go deeper in its focus and its exhibitions are all the better for it. Plan to spend about an hour and leave with a deeper appreciation of Finnish design.

name: Design Museum
review_text:
If you are into design, this is a must see! The permanent collection on the ground floor offers a journey through Finnish design from the 1870s to the modern day. You will realise how timeless some pieces are.

In the top floor is a special Exhibit featuring the works of Finnish design legend Eero Aarnio, creator of the iconic ball chair.  The display is highly creative, with the pieces on round platforms that rotate and move around the room responding to its guests. It's like a big Roomba!

The basement houses experimental art. It it worth taking a look.

Tip:  Be sure to check out the shop and cafe.

name: Design Museum
review_text: It’s one of its kind . The first place I went in Helsinki was the design museum. Must see!

name: Design Museum
review_text: Incredible exhibition of Kustaa Saksi now at design museum. It brings hope to those suffering of migraine to know that of such nuisance something this magnificent can surface.
owner_answer: Thank you for your review and lovely feedback!

name: Design Museum
review_text: One of the most lackluster, empty museums I have ever visited. Not worth the price at all, even with both museums included (Can both be completed within an hour)

name: Design Museum
review_text: As all reviews state, it is a small museum but worth the visit! Very informative and interesting to learn about Finnish design! A lot of iconic designs we did not realize. Spent 90 minutes there.

name: Design Museum
review_text: A small but lovely selection of modern design. The current special exhibit makes it worth the visit. I would have given it 5 stars of it were a bit larger. Free Wi-Fi is available so feel free to take a break in the café after your visit.

name: Design Museum
review_text: Interesting but for me it was not worth the €20.00 entrance fee - even accounting for the architectural museum entry too.

name: Design Museum
review_text: Simple, but beautiful little space with tells a clear and interesting story of Finnish design. We saw a beautiful exhibition on Eero Aarnio - a local Finnish superstar of modern design. Fun for older and younger alike, not just design geek!

name: Design Museum
review_text: We visited this compact museum located in a nice neighborhood with good restaurants, cafes and art galleries.  The museum is in three floors of a beutiful old house. It is small enough not to be exhausting. I think the permanent exhibition, which tells the story of the Finnish design, is perhaps more interesting for the locals who might own or have owned  many of its objects themselves. The changing exhibitions provide a wider set of the design world. It has a nice small cafe and a bookshop. All signs and infoboards are in English too.

name: Design Museum
review_text: the regular exhibition is the best, alawys worth visiting

name: Design Museum
review_text: Easily one of my favorite museums now. Great variety of exhibits, tons of air and space to take everything in and reflect. A lot of light, a few interesting tech innovations (yes, 3D is here!). A very good bookshop in the gift shop. All in all, a must see in Helsinki, and if you're a design afficcionado, it might just be the reason to come to Finland in the first place.

name: Design Museum
review_text: Wonderful, well-curated museum! Their exhibits captivated me from the moment I walked in, and kept my attention for hours. Their permanent collection was so intriguing- I had no clue so many iconic designs were from Finland! It gave me a much better understanding of their culture, and I’m so glad I went. The visiting exhibit on Josef Frank’s work was also interesting and enjoyable. I recommend this museum to anyone planning a visit to Helsinki.

name: Design Museum
review_text: Not worth the price (20€). Very few things displayed, the room with chair design was nice and fun.

name: Design Museum
review_text: Great museum with interesting exhibits, my favorite was the exhibition about the Finnish design and it evolution
owner_answer: Thank you for the visit and your review!

name: Design Museum
review_text:
Quite small but informative and revealing. So many cool things have originated in Finland, not just Nokia. The exhibition about gardens was very absorbing.

It is wheelchair accessible but you have to around the back to get in.

The ticket gets you in to the architecture museum behind it.

name: Design Museum
review_text:
It's a small but packed museum. There were three exhibits, detailing Finnish work throughout time. Of course, they discussed Marimekko and Fiskar, but I loved that they had a room dedicated to up and coming designers and projects. They didn't just have typical "art" works, but also discussed public projects and technology, and how human centered they were. I think to anyone who is interested/involved in art and design, you'll recognize a lot of the stuff but think "I didn't know that was Finnish!".

The admission was 10 euro, 5 for students. You can pay 12 euro to also get access to the adjacent architecture museum but I went and did not find it worth visiting.

name: Design Museum
review_text: Very nice museum with a nice exhibition. You can try a virtual machine. I liked the exhibition about scissors and what kind of art you can do with paper and scissors. One of the few museums with explanations in English.

name: Design Museum
review_text: Tapestries were fantastic. The rest of the display bit of a let down
owner_answer: Thank you for your review and feedback. Nice to hear that you liked the exhibition Kustaa Saksi: In the Borderlands!

name: Design Museum
review_text: Love their exhibition. Very interesting and you get to know some history and brand from Helsinki

name: Design Museum
review_text: It's relatively small museum but it is doing great for how lottle space it has. One week after the visit I was in design museum in Copenhagen. That is on cometely different level. Nonetheless if you are in Helsinki and love design I would say it's totallybworth the visit

name: Design Museum
review_text:
When I was there, the 2nd floor was closed for changing of exhibits. Only the ground floor’s permanent exhibition and basement’s “healing” exhibit was on show.

Ticket was at a lower price. 4euros for student.
Space and range of exhibit was quite small - could be finished in 30-45minutes.

Not the best design museum that I have been to. Could have more interactive elements.

name: Design Museum
review_text:
The Design Museum is another impressive Neo-Gothic edifice you’ll encounter in Helsinki. You can visit this museum together with the Architecture one, which is right next corner, with one combined ticket.
Finland is internationally famous for its cutting-edge design and the Design Museum showcases the nation’s history of industrial, fashion, and graphic design from the late 19th century to the present day.
owner_answer: Thank you for the review!

name: Design Museum
review_text: Really interesting. The entry tickets are a bit dear, but if. Your into designing stuff then definetaly worth it

name: Design Museum
review_text: Very interesting but sometimes confusing (at least as a foreigner). Definitely worth to go to.
owner_answer: Kiitos palautteesta! Thank you for the review!

name: Design Museum
review_text: Definitely worth visiting, especially if you're into design.

name: Design Museum
review_text: It was very interesting but I feel it didn't have enough about the major Finnish designers and their lives

name: Design Museum
review_text: Great introduction to the museum. Some work going on when we went so didn't see main collection.
owner_answer: Thank you for visiting us! We are just building our new main exhibition that will open on Friday May 5th, then again all three exhibitions available.

name: Design Museum
review_text: Very interesting introduction into finnish Design and its classic pieces.

name: Design Museum
review_text: Excellent collection! If you're interested in modern and european design this museum will be perfect choice. when I visited the exhibition about california culture was held and it was awesome. the signage system and interior are well organized. It's good to buy combination ticket for architecture museum nearby. highly recommend!

name: Design Museum
review_text: The museum is really overpriced for what it offers - the exhibition is small and not well described, not covering the subject well enough at all.

name: Design Museum
review_text: Small but beautifully formed collection of Finnish design classics and temporary exhibits of wider interest.
owner_answer: Thank you for visiting and leaving a review!

name: Design Museum
review_text: Were there during Helsinki Day, so museum was full of people. Many design projects were presented on the ground floor. Overall it was fun, you can even play Angry Birds with your friend. Carpets were displayed on the second floor. Interesting and not in every museum you will find this. Well suited for a one-time visit, especially if the entrance is free

Given its cultural significance, the museum is in some ways modest and I found the subdued lighting to be somewhat odd. As well as the museum’s collection there are also exhibitions and the venue is also a hub for research and discussion.

There is an excellent cafe and a small bookshop.

Also, most of the interactive installations were out of order. In my opinion, this wasn't worth the 15 euros entrance fee.
owner_answer: Thank you for your feedback - every feedback is important to us! Fragile objects like textiles are sensible to light. Our collection exhibition Utopia now, is not presented in chronological order, but in thematic order. The exhibition includes entities called "process", "virtuality", "icons", "new museum", "warehouse" and "museum timeline". With the admission fee you can also experience two other exhibitions. Hopefully next time we can do better!

name: Design Museum
review_text:
Kävin täällä maaliskuun alussa. Itse paikkakin oli hienossa talossa. Heti kassalta sain hyvää palvelua. Minulle selitettiin miten kannattaa toimia. Käytin Museokorttia.
Vaatteet voi jättää naulakkoon tai lukittaviin kaappeihin.

Näyttelyt olivat todella hyviä. Siitä sain hyvän kuvan Suomalaisesta muotoilusta. Esineistöä oli hyvin esillä. Itse innostuin kokeillemaan virtuaalilaseilla käykentelyä. Se oli hyvä.

Vaihtuva näyttely puutarhasta oli mielenkiintoinen ja puhutteleva.

name: Design Museum
review_text:
Pysyvä näyttely hyvä ja mielenkiintoinen.

Vaihtuva näyttely yläkerrassa ala-arvoinen. Likainen patja ja lastentarhan tasoisia piirustuksia olevinaan taidetta. Äänitaidetta se, että joku rapsuttaa tuolia. Paikkaustaidetta se, että parsittuja villasukkia vitriinissä jne.

Kaikki ei ole taidetta mitä päähän pälkähtää! Olin jo tarpeeksi tuohtunut tästä kun menin museokortilla, mutta jos olisin maksanut 20e tuontasoisesta "taiteesta" niin olisi veri alkanut kunnolla kiertää.

Jätä väliin kaikki muut paitsi se pysyvä design näyttely.

Man will hier auf Teufel komm' raus anders sein und geht dabei völlig am Sinn eines Museums vorbei. Sehr schade!
Das Viertel drumherum lässt sich übrigens schön zu Fuß erkunden. Das würde ich eher empfehlen, statt viel Geld für einen Nothingburger rauszuhauen. :)

name: Design Museum

Tipp: Alle finnischen Designmarken haben im Umkreis von wenigen Minuten tolle Geschäfte, in denen man alles kostenlos und top präsentiert sehen kann.

name: Design Museum
review_text:
Il Museo del Design di Helsinki è una gemma imperdibile per chiunque sia interessato al design e alla creatività. Situato nel cuore della città, il museo offre un viaggio affascinante attraverso la storia del design finlandese, con una particolare attenzione al design industriale, grafico e alla moda.

Appena si entra, si viene accolti da un ambiente moderno e ben curato, che rispecchia perfettamente l'essenza del design scandinavo: minimalista, funzionale ed elegante. Le esposizioni permanenti raccontano la storia del design finlandese dal XIX secolo fino ai giorni nostri, mostrando oggetti iconici e innovazioni che hanno segnato il mondo del design globale.

Una delle caratteristiche più interessanti del museo è la sua capacità di combinare tradizione e innovazione. Le mostre temporanee spesso esplorano temi contemporanei e sfide attuali, mettendo in luce come il design possa rispondere ai problemi sociali e ambientali di oggi.

Il museo è anche interattivo, con spazi dedicati ai visitatori di tutte le età. I bambini possono divertirsi con attività pensate per stimolare la loro creatività, mentre gli adulti possono partecipare a workshop e conferenze che offrono un approfondimento sul mondo del design.

Il personale del museo è estremamente cortese e disponibile, sempre pronto a offrire spiegazioni dettagliate e a rispondere a qualsiasi domanda. La caffetteria del museo è un altro punto forte, offrendo un'ampia scelta di dolci e bevande in un ambiente che riflette il design raffinato del museo.

In conclusione, il Museo del Design di Helsinki è un'attrazione che non può mancare nel vostro itinerario. Che siate appassionati di design o semplicemente curiosi, questo museo offre un'esperienza ricca e stimolante che vi lascerà con una nuova prospettiva sul mondo del design.

name: Design Museum
review_text: Mielenkiintoinen ja monipuolinen kokemus! Suosittelen varaamaan riittävästi aikaa tutustumiseen.

name: Design Museum

Nyt katsoja jäi passiiviseksi tekstien ja kuvien katsojaksi. Elävää luontoa ei ollut lainkaan. Vuorovaikutteisuus puuttui. Vaikkapa muovailuvahasta ja tarvikkeista vierailijat olisivat voineet tehdä oman tulkintansa puutarhasta tai osallistua yhteisen puutarhan rakentamiseen. Esimerkiksi säkillinen viljaa on puhdas ja melkein ilmainen aine.

Le café filtre au bar est gratuit. En face vous pourrez faire du patin a glace l hiver avec petite descente en luge

name: Design Museum
review_text:
ヘルシンキでまた訪れたい場所の一つ。実物のプロダクトの展示を見ながら、フィンランドデザインの流れを知ることができます。併設のミュージアムショップはコンパクトですが面白い商品がたくさんありました。

展示を見て思い出しましたが、そういえば、アングリーバードもフィンランド生まれですね。プロダクトデザインだけに偏っていないのも良かったです。

訪問した時はフィンランド出身のテキスタイルアーティストの特別展を開催していて、これがとても面白かったです。緻密でスケールの大きい作品は圧巻。宇宙や昆虫や気候問題や偏頭痛がデザインのモチーフになっていたりと、かなりユニークでタペストリーの印象が180度変わりました。

name: Design Museum

Die finnische Designabteilung war okay. Hier und da ganz interessant, jedoch nicht überaus spannend gestaltet. Somit auch eher ein Museum für das ältere Publikum ;)

Die zweite Abteilung übertraf da schon eher die Vorstellungen. Zukunftsvisionen wurden in moderner Kunst sehr spannend inszeniert. Sehr zu empfehlen, jedoch weiß ich nicht, ob dies eine Dauerausstellung war.

name: Design Museum
review_text:
Hyvä museo joka nimensä mukaisesti on keskittynyt suomalaisen designiin.
Vaihtuvat näyttelyt ovat myös hyviä. Tällä kertaa esillä oli Kustaa Saksin töitä.
Tiloissa myös kahvila ja kauppa.
owner_answer: Paljon kiitoksia arviostasi!

name: Design Museum
review_text: Uns wurde das Museum von einem Reiseführer empfohlen. Wir waren aber Recht enttäuscht. 20 Euro pro Person! Und letztendlich kommt man schnell durch. In dem extra Gebäude wurden Putzmaterialien ausgestellt... Für Menschen, die evtl Design studieren oder mit Design zusammenarbeiten, ist es bestimmt was. Für "Normalos" wie wir, aber nichts. Zumindest das Preis-Leistungsverhältnis stimmt unserer Meinung nicht.

name: Design Museum
review_text: Die Ausstellung ist nicht sehr groß. Man sieht auf 3 Etagen unterschiedliche Dinge. Eine Ausstellung  zeigt zur Zeit  die Arbeit eines Künstlers, wie er seine Migräne sieht, die er seit Kindheit hat. Es gibt Erklärungen auf Finnisch, schwedisch und Englisch. Der Eintritt hat 15€ für einen Erwachsenen gekostet. Es gibt Ermäßigung für Kinder und Studenten. . Alle sind freundlich dort. Ich finde kein Muss zu sehen, aber dennoch  ein wenig Zeitreise im Design und nette Abwechslung bei schlechtem Wetter.
owner_answer: Vielen Dank für das Feedback!

name: Design Museum
review_text: Une expo vue en décembre une en septembre,  les 2 magnifiques et avec une scénographie extraordinaire.  J'aime le design museo, ce bâtiment superbe, sa petite boutique et son café mais surtout le choix des expositions. Bravo!
owner_answer: Merci beaucoup! Thank you for your review and lovely feedback!

name: Design Museum
review_text: Zu teuer - 20€ pro Kopf gehen gar nicht. Das ist es nicht wert. Wir haben es auf eine Empfehlung hin bezahlt und waren schwer enttäuscht. Fängt im EG ganz gut an und danach kommt quasi nichts brauchbares mehr. 2€ wären angemessen.

name: Design Museum
review_text:
Perusnäyttelyssä kattava läpileikkaus suomalaiseen muotoiluun. Jo kassalla Fiskarsin sakset muodostavat varsinaisen taideteoksen!

Vaihtuvat näyttelyt mielenkiintoisia, nyt esittelyssä Nurmesniemet.

Kahvilan ja museokaupan tarjonta monipuolista.
owner_answer: Hei Jaana, kiitos arviosta ja mukavasta palautteestasi. Tervetuloa uudestaan!

name: Design Museum
review_text: Designmuseossa on esillä Fix-Huolla ja korjaa-näyttely yhteistyössä Arkkitehtuurimuseon kanssa.
owner_answer: Lämmin kiitos arviostasi!

name: Design Museum
review_text: Musée intéressant sur le design. Nous avons eu la chance de voir une très belle exposition de tapis de l'artiste Finlandais Kustaa SAKSI. De très belles oeuvre. Au rez-de-chaussée, l'exposition permanente présente de nombreuses œuvres. Au sous sol l'exposition de Tomi LEPPANEN est plus surprenante. Une agréable visite !

name: Design Museum
review_text:
Отличный музей. Экспозиции занимают три этажа. На 2 этаже постоянная выставка.
На 1 и 3 этажах экспозиции меняются.
Финам есть чем гордится в плане дизайна. Есть очень интересные экземпляры.
Мне понравился музей. Буду следить, когда смениться временная экспозиция и схожу ещё раз.
Хорошо бы прийти туда с гидом.
owner_answer: Kiitos palautteesta! Thank you for the review!

name: Design Museum
review_text:
Рядом с музеем Дизайна на отгороженной части проезжей части устроена с одной стороны зона одтыха с качелями, а с другой танцплощадка.
Здесь танцуют люди от 20 до 60, похоже раньше не знакомые. Кто-то пришёл специально, кто-то проходил мимо. Как же это здорово!
Основная экспозиция очень достойная, акцент на дизайн 60-80ых. Отдельно впечатляет экспозиция посвящённая знаменитым ножницам.
Временная была велеколепная выставка дизайнера ковров Kustaa Saksi, черпающего вдохновение из всего - из наблюдения за кузнечиком, из сказок и древней мифологии, из наблюдений природы, из музыки Сибелиуса, которую вдохновило поэтическое произведение, их детских приступов мигрени, из рассказа родственника о его галюцинациях.
Отдельное впечатление от ковра A World in Waiting, в котором автор попытался представить природу в 4017 году, основанное на изучении генезиса растений местной флоры, вдохновленный ренесансным ковром из коллекции Лондонского Альберт и Виктория Холла.
owner_answer: Thank you for your review and feedback!

name: Design Museum
review_text:
Franchement déçu
Vu la richesse du savoir-faire Finnois, les expos sont pauvres et très réduites.
On annonce 1 heure pour le design et 1h pour l'architecture, mais faut prévoir de lire toutes les explications, ouvrir tout les tiroirs
La scénographie est ratée. Des éléments sont trop bas, ou dans des tiroirs trop lourds a ouvrir, les ombres portées gènes la lecture.

Bref décevant pour le prix. Heureusement on peut jouer au Legos. Pour le reste pas vraiment de découvertes ou d'approfondissement

name: Design Museum
author_title: NORANEKO DESIGNノラネコデザイン
review_text:
案外小さい美術館ですが、コンパクトにデザインの歴史がまとまっています。
地下の照明を展示した空間が素敵なので見落とさないようにご注意ください。

ユーロも物価も高いため入場料が割高に感じますが、学生は国を問わず学生証があれば学生料金で入れます。コインロッカーは無料です。

name: Design Museum
review_text: Leuk museum, maar was er binnen 15 minuten weer op uitgekeken. Je kan ook naar het Architectuurmuseum als je een ticket koopt, maar vond dat nog minder interessant.

name: Design Museum
review_text: 開催中の企画展はそれ程興味あるテーマではありませんでした。混んでいたし。。。

name: Design Museum
review_text:
Pieni pettymys oli odotukset korkeammalla. Odotin että olisi ollut enemmän näytteillä suomalaisia desing esineitä.
Valitettavasti toisen kerroksen näyttelytilat olivat kokonaan suljettu.
Desingmuseoon ja arkkitehtimuseoon saa yhteislipun edullisemmin. Museot ovat aivan lähellä toisiaan.
owner_answer: Kiitos että jätit arvostelun! Museon toiseen kerrokseen avautuu 8.10. uusi päänäyttely "Intiimin kosketus," joka tuo kymmenien suomalaisten muoti- ja asustesuunnittelijoiden työt näytille. Tervetuloa pian uudelleen!

name: Design Museum
review_text:
フィンランドのモダンなデザインを観るにはとてもオススメです！

小さなお子さんでも楽しめると思います！

記憶は確かではないですが確か1500円ぐらいです。ロッカーもあるので荷物を預けてゆっくりと観て回れます。アクセスもいい場所にあるので、移動に疲れたらここでゆっくりするのをオススメします！

人も多くはないので良かったです！

name: Design Museum
review_text:
Небольшой музей, здание старое, но внутри все современное. На первом и втором этаже выставки финского дизайна, в подвале - новые подающие надежды дизайнеры. Много мест, чтобы запостить в инстаграм.
Проводят экскурсии на английском, но в принципе можно спокойно обойтись без экскурсовода, выставка очень понятная.
Неплохой музей магазин, но ничего особенного нет.
По-настоящему захватывают произведения искусства.

name: Design Museum
review_text: 結構面白い美術館でしたが、20ユーロの入場料はちょっと高すぎる気がします。デザインを勉強している人なら元が取れると思います😊
owner_answer: Thank you for your review and feedback! The museum ticket includes entry to both the Design Museum and the neighboring Museum of Finnish Architecture.

name: Design Museum
review_text: Странен и неразбираем. Част от експонатите бяха твърде алтернативни за мен и дори смушаващи. Ако не сте с Хелзинки карт не препоръчвам да си губите парите.

name: Design Museum
review_text: Musee très intéressant sur le Design finlandais. En plus, c'était gratuit le jour où nous y sommes allés ! (Dernier mardi ou mercredi du mois il me semble)
owner_answer: Thank you for your feedback!  In 2023 we offer free entry every last Tuesday of each month from 11 am to 8 pm. Also we offer free entry on some special occasions like on the Night of Arts in August and Experience 6 Museums Night in November 2023.

name: Design Museum
review_text:
很推～
設計的常設展、特別展都很到位！
可以了解芬蘭的在地品牌的故事
甚至其實跟當地的文化、生活習慣也息息相關
這裡充滿很美麗的設計 🌞

name: Design Museum
review_text: 入口が分かりにくいですが、階段を登って左側に案内があります。外国人がフィンランドの文化を知るにはとても良い美術館だと思います。
owner_answer: Kiitos palautteestasi! Thank you for the review and feedback!

name: Design Museum
review_text: Розташовано недалеко від центрального вокзалу, 3 зупинки трамваєм. Квіток 20 евро, якщо ще забажаєте відвідати музей архітектури, який до речі не сподобався. Що до музею дизайну, так сподобалась виставка килимів. Хочу звернути увагу на крамничку в музеї, цікава підбірка тематичних видань. Раджу відвідати.
owner_answer: Thank you for your review and feedback!

name: Design Museum
review_text: Это первый музей, который меня не зацепил от слова совсем. Ничего интересного. Грустно, уныло. Сегодня был бесплатный вход, чем я и воспользовался. А если бы я ещё и за вход заплатил - поставил бы кол! Всё посмотрел за 10 минут.
owner_answer: Thank you for the review, every feedback is valuable to us. Hopefully next time we can do better. We have three exhibition floors, hopefully you managed to visit them all.

name: Design Museum
review_text:
В музее три этажа экспозиции. На подвальном сейчас идёт выставка работ дизайнера предметов для интерьера. Очень красиво и по-фински: вроде бы очень просто, но какая красота и как естественно (а потому умиротворяюще) выглядит.

Первый этаж - постоянная экспозиция истории финского дизайна. В основном предметы интерьера, но есть и немного одежды с украшениями. Интересно. Есть даже небольшой интерактивчик:)

Второй этаж закрыт, готовится новая выставка. Поэтому билет вместо 12€ стоил 10€.

Мне очень понравилось!

Единственный минус: на русском материалов нет, а пояснения короткие. В идеале, нужен гид.

name: Design Museum
review_text:
Musée intéressant
Le sous-sol permet d’interagir, toucher aux éléments, j’ai beaucoup aimé
Ma visite a duré environ 1h.
Je suis allée le dernier mardi du mois donc c’était gratuit

name: Design Museum
review_text: Ein ungewöhnliches - und deshalb für uns - spannendes Museum. Wir haben eine Menge über finnische Designs gelernt und diese während unseres Aufenthalts in Finnland - aber auch außerhalb von Finnland - wiedergefunden. Schön auch die Interaktive Wand - "was wäre wenn ..."
owner_answer: Vielen Dank! Thank you for your review and feedback!

name: Design Museum
review_text: Upea designnäyttely, Suomen tunnettua muotoilua, mm paljon Iittalaa. Nanso 100v näyttely jäi kyllä kaipaamaan värejä ja muotoja vuosien takaa,olisi voinut toteuttaa laajemmin. Erittäin hyvä asiakaspalvelu.
owner_answer: Kiitos paljon! Toivottavasti tulet pian uudestaan!

name: Design Museum
review_text: Mielenkiintoiset ja havainnolliset esitykset erilaisista entisöinneistä. Hyvä ja viihtyisä kahvila. Korkeatasoinen WC. Kannatti ehdottomasti käydä ja viihdyin pitkään korkeatasoisen sivistyksen äärellä.

name: Design Museum
review_text: Très cher pour ce que c'est. Le musée du design ressemble plus à un musée d'art contemporain que du design. Le musée d'architecture est un peu plus intéressant mais franchement pas extraordinaire.

name: Design Museum
review_text: Entinen koulurakennus josta on kehkeytynyt yksi Stadin hienoimpia museoita. Kaikki yksityiskohdat ovat viimeisen päälle mietittyjä ja vaikka näyttelyt hieman toistavatkin itseään, viimevuosilta on jäänyt monta vaikuttavaa esillelaittoa mieleen. Alakerrassa on tosi kiva Tapio Anttilan näyttely missä saa kokeillakin huonekaluja.

name: Design Museum
review_text: Esperaba mucho más de un museo del diseño en este país.

name: Design Museum
review_text: Mielenkiintoinen museo. Muotoilua ja tietoa on tarjolla ja vielä vähän aikaa puutarhaihmisille erillinen näyttely puutarhojen eri vaiheista ja työvälineistä sekä katsaus menneeseen ja tulevaan.

name: Design Museum
review_text: 솔직히, 헬싱키의 디자인 뮤지엄에 기대를 많이해서인지 아쉬운 점이 더 많았어요. 핀란드를 대표하는 디자인이 상업적으로 유명세가 있는 회사나 디자이너로 이루어져서 그렇겠죠. 오히려 상설 전시가 더 재밌었네요. 어떤 전시가 있는지 확인하고 가는 것을 추천드립니다. 기본 전시는 솔직히 입장료가 너무 비싸다는 느낌이 드는 수준이거든요.
owner_answer: Thank you for your review and feedback. The existing and upcoming exhibitions can be found from our website.

name: Design Museum
review_text: Vermutlich kommt man im Land des Designs nicht ab diesem Museum vorbei. Die Präsentation der ausgestellten Werke ist ansprechend. Wenn man sich Zeit nimmt, kann man viel über Design und finnische Designhistorie erfahren. Manches ist sehr ansprechend, bei manchen Ausstellungsstücken fehlt mir der Zugang so sehr, dass ich den Wert nicht erkennen kann.

name: Design Museum
review_text: 去的时间太短了没看过来，可能是我英语不好看的太慢了或者也许是特殊展览，感觉第二层主要展出的是现代技术的进步（展示设计的新途径）很多美国的，有个AR sandbox很有趣，可以根据你造成的变动改变投影～大概一层才主要是芬兰设计～很多很有趣的设计。商店非常值得一逛和一买！

name: Design Museum
review_text: Un must assoluto della capitale finlandese. Da vedere non tanto per la collezione (il museo è piccolo se paragonato ad altri simili in Europa), quanto piuttosto per le idee che sono alla base della cultura nordica degli oggetti e del modo di vivere. Meravigliose le sculture in vetro di Simo Sarpaneva.

name: Design Museum
review_text:
핀에어 환승대기 시간이 길어 잠시 디자인뮤지엄에 Com_pa_ny 의 전시를 보기위해 방문을 했다. 부활절 기간이지만 뮤지엄은 오픈해있어서 다행이었다.
1층에는 핀란드의 디자인 히스토리에 대한 전시가 있고 2층에는 기획전시가 열린다. 갈때마다 보는 1층전시는 매번 다른 제품들이 눈에 들어와서 새로운 느낌이었다.
2층의 전시는 핀란드 디자이너 Olin 과 한국 디자이너 Aamu 부부의 작품들로 귀여운 상상의 제품들이 눈을 즐겁게 했다. 전시를 본 후 뮤지엄샵에서 눈송이 장난감을 사들고 나왔다.
이 곳은 헬싱키를 방문한다면 꼭 들려야 하는 곳이다.

name: Design Museum
review_text: Avis partagé sur ce musée, d'un côté on y découvre l'histoire du design en Finlande, mais c'est très (très) court. Il manque beaucoup de choses, d'objets, d'objets d'art mais aussi objets fonctionnels, d'explications, de film, ... On se sent lésé alors qu'il y a mille choses que l'on aurait aimé découvrir...

name: Design Museum
review_text: Spodziewałem się czegoś więcej niż trzech mebli głośników i telewizora.

name: Design Museum
review_text:
Kustaa Saksin näyttely oli erinomainen!

Myös kiinteä perusnäyttely on hyvä, mutta kerran kiertely riittää.

Mukavaa, että museo on auki maanantaisin (ainakin kesällä 2023), jolloin muut museot ovat kiinni.
owner_answer: Kiitos palautteestasi! Haluammekin kesällä tarjota mahdollisuuden viihtyä meillä joka päivä. Arkisin myös pidemmällä aikataululla.

name: Design Museum
review_text:
공사중이라 무료입장했습니다.
디자인 강국 핀란드의 역사에 대해 볼수있는 중요한 시간이었어요.
2023년엔 항구쪽에 산업디자인박물관인가? 암튼 이거랑 합쳐진다고 합니다.
정말 오래된 건물이라 그전에 한번 방문하시는거 추천드려요
기념품샵에 이쁜거 많습니다
owner_answer: Kiitos palautteesta! Thank you for the review! The new museum for architecture and design in Helsinki is something we are looking forward to, but it is still at the planning phase. You can follow the project here: https://www.admuseo.fi/eng-site/homepage

name: Design Museum
review_text:
Travel Music with: Daria Zawailow-Helsinki
북유럽의 비싼 물가에 부응하듯 입장료가 비싸지만, 볼 거리가 많지 않아 조금 실망하게 된다. 북유럽은 가구와 인테리어와 색감이 예술의 하나의 큰 기조로 자리잡고 있는데, 디자인 뮤지엄에는 이 모든 것이 엉성하고 부족했다. 오히려 무료로 개방된 공간이 좀 더 실하게 잘 구성된 느낌이었다

Admission is as expensive as it lives up to high prices in Northern Europe, but there isn't much to see, which makes me a little disappointed. Northern Europe is home to furniture, interior and color as one of the great pillars of art, all of which were sloppy and lacking in the design museum. Rather, the free open space felt more solidly organized.

name: Design Museum
review_text: La collezione permanente è interessante, interattiva ma breve. L'esibizione temporanea più interessante, ma piccola. Esperienza positiva, ma il prezzo è alto per quanto visto.

name: Design Museum
review_text: Ну, что сказать…такое разочарование, полный бред…Я даже не знаю как  описать свое состояние… это самое мое плохое впечатление от города!!! прошло несколько лет, а впечатление от этого музея осталось только негативное!!! я в шоке! я очень люблю дизайн, но...что это было? очень жаль потраченного драгоценного времени в этом городе на этот музей! ничего красивого или стоящего не вынесла из него, а только плохое настроение...это обидно!!!максимально магазинчик нас порадовал....

name: Design Museum
review_text: El lugar ideal para disfrutar del diseño finés, uno de los estilos de diseño mas exquisitos del mundo. Las colecciones en exposición maravillan. Muy variada y deliciosamente seleccionada. Un pequeño país escandinavo que marcó un rumbo muy definido apenas comenzado el siglo veinte. Y no se detuvo.

name: Design Museum
review_text: Où l'on comprend l'avant gardisme de la Finlande et comment le design a pour objectif le bien être et la durabilté👍

name: Design Museum
review_text: Está bien si te gusta el Arte Moderno, si no te gusta mucho o no lo emtiendes te agotarás enseguida pues no es especialmente ameno, participativo o con juegos creativos de iluminación.
owner_answer: Muchas gracias! Thank you for the review!

name: Design Museum
review_text: Oli hieno, ajatuksia herättävä FIX näyttely, "salivahti" oli erittäin hyvä, keskusteluun antautuva, jäi pitkä muisto käynnistä

name: Design Museum
review_text: Sympathique et intéressant sans être incontournable.

name: Design Museum
review_text:
Finsk design er med rette berømt og beundret.
Dette kan desværre ikke ses på de to finske design museer.
Kedelige…

name: Design Museum
review_text:
Skuffende oplevelse. Dette museum formidler på ingen måde finsk designs store omfang & betydning.
Vi læste at der er et nyt museum på vej... det er virkelig tiltrængt.

name: Design Museum
review_text:
Ich bin froh darüber durch die Helsinki-Card für dieses Museum nicht extra Geld ausgegeben zu haben. Ich habe wirklich mehr erwartet.
Die Atmosphäre im Museum ähnelt der eines beschäftigten Bahnhofs und die Präsentation der einzelnen Gegenstände wirkt lieblos und wird dem Anspruch großes Design zu vermitteln einfach nicht gerecht. Schade, da das finnische Design doch eigentlich wirklich eine Menge zu bieten hat.

Für alle die sinnlose ASMR Installationen über Möbelstücke oder dem Reparatur-prozess eines Game-Boys lauschen wollen.. für den ist hier sicherlich was dabei..

name: Design Museum
review_text: Beau panorama du design finlandais et magnifique exposition de tapisseries à l étage.  Lunch salade délicieuse au cafe Taito pour 11€

name: Design Museum
review_text: Plusieurs expositions : l’une sur l’histoire du design finlandais (Nokia, Fiskars, Angry birds …), seconde expo sur les designers de mode et une troisième sur les teintures naturelles basées sur d’anciennes recettes.

name: Design Museum
review_text: Il museo si suddivide in tre allestimenti in altrettanti piani: al -1 delle mostre  temporanee brevi, piano terra la mostra del design scandinavo con pochi pezzi, al piano superiore una mostra monografica temporanea semi-permanente. Una grandissima delusione. Per via del COVID i dispositivi multimediali erano indisponibili.

name: Design Museum
review_text: Companyn näyttely oli ajatuksia herättävä monella tavalla. Pidin näyttelystä. Varsinkin näyttelyarkkitehtuuri oli loistava. Tämä pariskunta on ollut suosikkini jo vuosia. Aamu Songin punainen puku ei unohdu koskaan

name: Design Museum
review_text: Mielenkiintoinen ja yllättävä näyttely tällä kertaa.

name: Design Museum
review_text: интересный магазинчик при музеи, даже интереснее, чем сам музей. Понравилась выставка в подвальном этаже про океан. А вот основная экспозиция скучная. В красном кресле можно сидеть - внутри классно

name: Design Museum
review_text: Monipuolinen kiva pikku museo. Kokemus jäi rajatuksi, kun vain pieni osa näyttelystä oli auki. Palaan siis myöhemmin vielä uudestaan.
owner_answer: Kiitos käynnistä ja tervetuloa uudelleen! Uusi päänäyttely "Intiimin kosketus" aukeaa 8.10. Kiitos että jätit arvostelun!

name: Design Museum
review_text: No está mal, aunque me pareció un poco caro (20€ adultos, 12€ estudiantes) para el tamaño del museo. Expone piezas de cualquier tipo (ropa, muebles, juegos...) de diseño finlandes.

name: Design Museum
review_text: Designmuseo on upea rakennus sekä ulkoa että sisältä. Alakerrassa on pysyvä näyttely jota ei ole kehitetty vuosiin ja yläkerrassa taitaa olla vaihtuva näyttely. Tällä kerta (11/2021) oli yläkerrassa kokonainen mallisto todella kummallisia asuja. Kellarikerroksen näyttely upeassa tiiliholvi tilassa oli mitään sanomaton.

name: Design Museum
review_text: Upeaa, että puutarhataide on esillä niin A:ssa kuin D:ssäkin! LISÄÄ!

name: Design Museum
review_text: Posto molto bello ed esposizioni  interessanti ; spazio un po' piccolo x il costo del biglietto  ( 20 eur)

name: Design Museum
review_text: Сучасний Арт простір. Бажано володіти однією з трьох мов, якими подається інформація. Інакше може бути не дуже цікаво.

name: Design Museum
review_text: Le musée du Design est une curiosité si vous vous intéressez aux objets créatifs. Au premier étage j’ai vu une exposition d’un tapissier extraordinaire à voir absolument. Pour le prix j’ai payé 20€.
owner_answer: Thank you for your great review and exhibition recommendation to the Kustaa Saksi: In the Borderlands exhibition! Our basic ticket costs 15 euros, and the 20 euros ticket is a combine-ticket that covers both the Design Museum and the Museum of Finnish Architecture.

name: Design Museum
review_text:
Si vous êtes pas un  intellectuel du design  vous allez en ressortir comme le musée le souhaitais : avec pleins d'interrogations ,
Les textes sont remplis de questions non répondus , les objets semblent VRAIMENT anodins et  en faible nombre,
Bref c'était soit disant un incontournable mais je suis très déçu.

name: Design Museum
review_text:
Entrada gratuita el último martes del mes. Estaba confundido.

Disfruté de las exposiciones sobre el diseño finlandés.
owner_answer: Thank you for your review and feedback!

name: Design Museum
review_text: 비싼 입장료에 비해 관람양이 많지 않음. 무료와이파이와 화장실 이용이 가능함. 디자인을 좋아하는 사람에게는 방문할 가치가 있겠으나, 개인적으로 나는 별로였음.

name: Design Museum
review_text: 展示の方法が凝っていて、すごくオシャレだった。テキスタイルデザインが好きな人は特に楽しめると思う。プロダクトデザインよりもテキスタイルが多め。
owner_answer: Thank you for your review and feedback!

name: Design Museum
review_text: Keräilijät ja kokoelmat näyttely on mielenkiintoinen, suosittelen että menet opastetulle kierrokselle niin saat kuulla myös esineiden ja keräilijöiden taustoista enemmän tietoa.

name: Design Museum
review_text: Oli pienoinen pettymys, mutta odotukset olivat korkealla. Suurin osa suomalaisista klassikoista oli edustettuna, mutta paljon jäi vielä piiloon. Olisin toivonut esille enemmän huonekaluja (Domus, Aslsk -tuoit, Aallon tuotantoa)  ja lasiesineitä (Toikan upeat vuosikuutiot, Nancy Still jne). Taisi olla, ettei lamppujakasn ollut esillä kovin paljon.

name: Design Museum
review_text: Leuk museum met ook uitleg hoe design werkt. Met speciale vragen voor kinderen. Alle onderschriften in 3 talen waarvan 1 Engels. Mooi dus!

name: Design Museum
review_text: ショップとカフェは無料で利用できます。ショップはフィンランド土産が凝縮した感じで売ってます。なかなかステキでした。

name: Design Museum
review_text: Esplorare il museo del design è come vivere un'esperienza con ciò che ha fatto la storia del design in finlandia. Ospitato in un bel palazzo neogotico, risulta sicuramente ben organizzato e ben strutturato, ma se non si è appassionati del tema, meglio evitarlo. Il biglietto è completamente gratis con la Helsinki card.

name: Design Museum
review_text: Laba pieredze uzzināt, kuras lietas dizainiski ir iekarojušas pasauli.

name: Design Museum
review_text: que lugar tan decepcionante… ni se les ocurra venir, es demasiado chico y sin chiste. ni la tienda está bonita! nada que ver con otros lugares similares como el de copenhague. te incluye la entrada al de arquitectura que está atrás y ni así. de verdad, no gastes tu dinero, busca otra cosa que hacer

name: Design Museum
review_text: Museo non molto ampio con poche opere rispetto al prezzo del biglietto pagato 15 euro. All'interno comunque vi sono pezzi di vero pregio del disign
owner_answer: Thank you for your review and feedback!

name: Design Museum
review_text: Lite litet men annars mycket bra!

name: Design Museum
review_text: サクッと寄るのにちょうど良いスケールの美術館です。企画展が主で、その時々によって大きく印象が変わるようです。美術館の反対には大きな協会があり、このエリアの佇まいも素敵です。

name: Design Museum
review_text:
Beau musée qui retrace une partie des inovations/développement des entreprises/artistes finlandais qui ont marqué le histoire.
Un peu déçus par le petit espace réservés aux Aalto
owner_answer: Kiitos palautteesta! Thank you for the review!

name: Design Museum
review_text:
Visita imprescindible para los amantes del diseño. Por segunda vez, aprovechando viaje a #Slush19 fui una tarde a visitar elMuseo. Además, con la acreditación de Slush era gratis!

Pude ver 3 exposiciones; todas ellas muy interesantes. No pude explayarme mucho ya que solo tenía una hora pero me dio para verlas.

Hoy toca visita casa-estudio Alvar Aalto!

name: Design Museum
review_text:
Mahtava esittely Su
omalaisten luomista designista käytännön elämään

name: Design Museum
review_text: Ben je geïnteresseerd in design breng dan hier een bezoek. Weet je nog hoe de eerste Nokia mobiele telefoon er uit zag ?
owner_answer: Thank you for the your feedback and review!

name: Design Museum
review_text: Nicht sonderlich interessant. Dank Helsinki Card hatten wir zumindest kein Geld dafür ausgegeben

name: Design Museum
review_text: Yksitähti siitä että pääsi museokortilla   aika mitään sanomaton minun makuun

name: Design Museum
review_text: Un museo interessante ma molto minimal considerando che siamo in una delle capitali del design. Decisamente interessante la mostra di saski dove sono esposti magnifici lavori realizzati al telaio
owner_answer: Thank you for your review and lovely feedback!

name: Design Museum
review_text: Kültürel bir çalışma göremedim. Daha çok yenilikçi ve modern tasarımlar vardı…

name: Design Museum
review_text: On hyvä tuntea muotoilun historiaa ja myös nykyaikaa.

name: Design Museum
review_text: Vacker byggnad i bästa kvarteren i Helsingfors. Genomarbetad basutställning och definitivt värt ett besök!

name: Design Museum
review_text: 我在2018年9月去參觀，展場不大只有一樓和二樓的展覽空間，有分常態展和特展，常態展介紹芬蘭的一些經典設計，服務人員很親切，也有置物櫃可以寄放背包，大概可以逛一小時左右。

name: Design Museum
review_text: A não perder. Ir à tarde e pode ser que possa dançar - ou ver dançar cá fora - a partir das 5pm
owner_answer: Thank you for your feedback and great review!

name: Design Museum
review_text: Großes Museum mit vielfältiger Kunst. Manchmal keine Kunst.
owner_answer: Kiitos palautteestasi! Thank you for the review and feedback!

name: Design Museum
review_text:
앵그리버드부터 메리메꼬까지... 핀란드 디자인 역사를 찬찬히 살펴볼 수 있는 박물관.
규모는 크지않지만 다양한 전시품이 볼만하다.
지하에는 체험공간(?)같은 곳이 있었는데 관광객도 참여할 수 있는지는 모르겠음.

name: Design Museum
review_text: Не большой музей, очень насыщенный. Людям разбегающихся в дизайне будет интересно, простой обыватель за пол часа пробежит все залы. На удивление туристов в нем было наибольшее количество, заслуженно ли это?! Решать вам после посещения.

name: Design Museum
review_text: Et veldig interessant museum. Har et eget rom der barn kan få leke seg.

name: Design Museum
review_text: Этот музей не изобилует огромным количеством экспонатов (за 30-50 минут уложитесь), но если Вы в той или иной степени интересуетесь дизайном, то это место обязательно для посещения. Немного расстраивает, что почти всё представленное относится только к 20-му веку.

name: Design Museum
review_text: Godne obejrzenia, cena 12 euro dość wysoka, ale jak na Helsinki to standard.
owner_answer: bardzo dziękuję! Thank you very much!

name: Design Museum
review_text: Було цікаво, але очікувала чогось wow. Пройшлись з подружкою трошки пофотагруфували.
owner_answer: Thank you for visiting us!

name: Design Museum
review_text: Hienossa rakennuksessa museo.

name: Design Museum
review_text: Museo spettacolare, bellissimo anche l'ingresso e il bar, raccomandato!

name: Design Museum
review_text: Hienoa saada olla kehissä mukana🙂👍! Puhtain terveisin, Roskasakin henkilökunta.

name: Design Museum
review_text: Каждый вторник вход в музей безплатный. Музей открыт с 11.00 до 20.00
owner_answer: Hello, thank you for your  review! The admission is free every last Tuesday of each month for the whole day (not every Tuesday). We hope you enjoyed your visit!

name: Design Museum
review_text: Upea ja mielenkiintoinen museo. Saksin näyttely erityisesti.
owner_answer: Paljon kiitoksia arviostasi ja ihanasta palautteesta!

name: Design Museum
review_text: Interessante pra quem gosta de design nórdico. Havia algumas peças icônicas em exibição. Da pra contemplar tudo com calma em 1h.

name: Design Museum
review_text: Schöne Ausstellung zum finnischen Design und dessen Protagonisten. Allerdings 20 EUR Eintritt

name: Design Museum
review_text: Πολύ καλό μουσείο που σε ταξιδεύει στο σχεδιαστικό κόσμο των Φιλανδών

name: Design Museum
review_text:
博物館內放置了很多知名設計師的作品
非常棒的設計博物館
對於喜歡設計的人來說是一定不可錯的景點之一

name: Design Museum
review_text: Интересный музей, но мы попали на смену экспозиции. Поэтому нам было мало экспонатов. Но посетить стоит.

name: Design Museum
review_text: Nouvelle politique de prix : on doit payer l’entrée de 2 musées (Design + Architecture) obligatoirement, que vous puissiez faire les 2 ou non … - avant c’était 15€ pour le Musée du Design seulement. Le tout à peine expliqué (alors que l’ancien prix est encore affiché ….). Bien dommage de donner le sentiment aux visiteurs de se faire avoir ……

name: Design Museum
review_text: Музей хорош своими экспанатами. Не все залы, конечно, показались мне интересными, но в план помещений в г. Хельсинки включить его стоит. Можно нарисовать на листочке картинку и прикрепить на стену :)

name: Design Museum
review_text: Olipa mukava museo, taas paljon "tuttua" nähtävää vuosien varrelta.

name: Design Museum
review_text: Petit musée mais très instructif sur l'histoire du design. Pour un néophyte comme moi, un bel éclairage sur me design.

name: Design Museum
review_text: Ihastuttava paikka! Eritoten 3 kerroksen keramiikka osasto hiveli silmiä! Schilkin super!
owner_answer: Kiitos palautteesta! 3. kerroksen Talvipuutarhaan ja niiden yhteydessä oleviin toimistoihin pääsee tutustumaan ajoittaisten kierrosten yhteydessä, erityisesti osana vuotuisia Open House Helsinki -tapahtumia. Juuri nyt päänäyttelyssä Kaiken kansan muotoilua (2 krs) on esillä myös laajasti keramiikkaa. Kiitos käynnistä ja tervetuloa uudelleen!

name: Design Museum
review_text: Aina hieno käydä, vaihtuvat näyttelyt yllättävät joka kerta!

name: Design Museum
review_text: 經過而已🤣😂🤣😂

name: Design Museum
review_text: Un "must" si visitas Helsinki. Oportunidad para conocer parte del historia del diseño finlandés y el origen de elementos que usamos todos los días como tijeras, teléfonos etc. Además, se mantienen exposiciones temporales de todo el mundo.

name: Design Museum
review_text:
15€ jetez à la poubelle !
Musée très petit, le première étage et assez rapide et le deuxième on y voit que des tapis !!!
on peut y apprendre tout de même quelque aspect intéressant sur le design finlandais mais ça ne vaut clairement pas 15€ !!
Très déçu !
owner_answer: Thank you for your feedback, sorry to hear that you were not happy with our content. Hopefully next time we can do better!

name: Design Museum
review_text:
Très déçu par ce musée, je ne recommande pas d’y aller.

En effet, l’entrée coûte 20€ pour un adulte et les expositions sont très décevantes.
L’exposition principale occupe le 1er étage et le tour est fait en 20mn maximum.

Le reste de l’exposition est très spécial et ne comporte rien qui soit en lien avec le design…

En bref, 20€ pour 20 minutes et une déception maximale.

Le prix n’est pas la question car même si l’entrée avait été gratuite, je j’aurais pas conseillé ce musée qui n’illustre absolument pas la richesse et la diversité du design Finlandais, je conseillerais plutôt d’aller visiter les boutiques spécialisées que ce musée.

name: Design Museum
review_text:
Hieno näyttely, hyvä opastus.
Kuvat Nurmesmiemen näyttelystä
owner_answer: Hei Tarja, kiitos mukavasta palautteesta ja arviostasi, tervetuloa uudestaan! Uusi päänäyttelymme, Kustaa Saksi: Rajamailla on nyt avoinna.

name: Design Museum
review_text: Ikonisia juttuja.

name: Design Museum
review_text: Viivyin pitkään katsomassa näyttelyä ystäväni kanssa. Katselin myös tarkkaan rakennuksen arkkitehtuuria, koska en ollut käynyt siellä muutamaan vuoteen. Oli ihanaa syödä sen jälkeen ja keskustella rauhassa.  Söin hyvää keittoa ja lounashintaan kuului leipää ja voita, suklaakarkki ja herkullinen leivos.
owner_answer: Kiitos arviostasi ja ihanasta palautteesta!

name: Design Museum
review_text: Интересный музей. Хоть и не большой, но почти все можно потрогать)))

name: Design Museum
review_text: 很棒的博物館，喜愛設計的人可以耗一整個上午！

name: Design Museum
review_text: Musée intéressant et qui peut être visité en un temps restreint.
owner_answer: Thank you for your visit, as well as the feedback!

name: Design Museum
review_text:
Vaihtuvat kiinnostavat näyttelyt, perusnäyttely ihanan nostalginen suomalaisesta arjen designista.

Museokorttilla helppo vilkaista, niin ei harmita jos vaihtuva näyttely olisikin huti.

name: Design Museum
review_text:
핀란드의 여러 유명 디자이너가 있는 곳
나쁘진 않았다

name: Design Museum
review_text: 免費參觀而且蠻有創意的，可以來走走

name: Design Museum
review_text: Leuk design museum met diverse exposities! 2 etages, een mini-shop en klein café. Per persoon betaal je €20 en studenten kunnen voor €6 naar binnen. Je bent ongeveer in één uur klaar. Makkelijke aansluiting met het centrum van Helsinki (loopafstand).
owner_answer: Thank you for your nice feedback! Our normal ticket costs 15 euros, under 18 years old free of charge. 20 euros ticket combines entry to both the Design Museum and the Museum of Finnish Architecture.

name: Design Museum
review_text: Финляндия дала миру дизайна несравнимо больше, чем то, что представлено в этом музее. Приезжая в Хельсинки я возлагал на этот музей большие надежд и был немного разочарован увиденным.

name: Design Museum
review_text:
Turkish below

It was nice but we expected more. There are so many Finish designs that affected the world. Some of them were shown here but in quite a simple way. All these designs deserve a better presentation.
The place is not very big you can visit in 1 hr. If you are visiting Helsinki you should see it.

Beklediğimiz kadar etkileyici değildi. Finlandiya'ya has o kadar çok tasarım varki biz daha çarpıcı bir müze bekliyorduk. Gezmesi 1 st suruyor. Helsinki deyseniz gidip gorun.

name: Design Museum
review_text: Kustaa Saksin omaperäinen näyttely kannattaa käydä katsomassa.
owner_answer: Kiitos arviostasi ja suosituksesta!

name: Design Museum
review_text: Vähän oli tylsähkö. Varmaan asiantunteville mielenkiintoisempi.

name: Design Museum
review_text: Suosittelen ehdottomasti Helsinki Design Museumia kaikille muotoilusta kiinnostuneille. Se on loistava paikka oppia lisää muotoilusta ja sen roolista elämässämme.

name: Design Museum
review_text: Museo molto interessante. Si può acquistare con tre euro in più, il biglietto comulativo per vedere anche il vicino museo di architettura.

name: Design Museum
review_text:
Kustaa Saksi näyttely todella upea! Näyttelylle 5 tähteä!!!
Minua häiritsi ruoanhaju näyttelytiloissa ja koko museossa. Epämiellyttävää! Olisiko mahdollista pitäytyä vain kahvissa ja pullassa?

name: Design Museum
review_text: J'ai bien aimé la visite de ce musée car sur certains éléments de design, il y a un grand nombre d'objets, d'outils,  de meubles,  etc dont l'origine finnoise ou des pays limitrophes de la Finlande est parfois insoupçonnée. Une vraie visite historique qui fait parfois resurgir des souvenirs d'enfance. Le musée va déménager et il est demandé au gens de faire  des propositions sur ce qu'ils souhaitent voir sur le nouveau site. C'est top.
owner_answer: Thank you very much for your review and feedback!

name: Design Museum
review_text: Nurmesniemen näyttely oli juuri menossa.

name: Design Museum
review_text: Leikkaus Suomen muotoilusta. Pala historiaa nähtävillä. Myös oma matka menneisyyteen. Ihanan pikkuinen talo kierrettäväksi.

name: Design Museum
review_text: Uskoisin et hyvä sijainti ja paikkaa

name: Design Museum
review_text: 작고 작업이 많진 않지만 좋았어요. 어떤 전시 하느냐에 따라 많이 다를 것 같아요

name: Design Museum
review_text:
Spart euch die 20€.
Das ist nahe an Betrug für die wenigen Exponate!!!

name: Design Museum
review_text: 20 euros l'entrée pour pas grand chose

name: Design Museum
review_text: Museo veramente scarso di contenuti e quelli che ci sono sono mal organizzati e non sempre in Inglese. Potrebbe andare bene per 5€ ma comunque spiacerebbe vedere una cosa così misera sopratutto considerando che la città di Helsinki e in quartiere del museo sono pieni di studi e oggetti di design.
owner_answer: Thank you for the review, every feedback is valuable to us. Hopefully next time we can do better. Inside the museum every exhibition text and museum signpost is provided also in English.

name: Design Museum
review_text: Intéressant mais très court
owner_answer: Thank you for your review and feedback.

name: Design Museum
review_text: フィンランドのプロダクトデザインをカバー。マリメッコやイッタラなどもある。

name: Design Museum
review_text: 흥미로운 주제가 많습니다 시간남으시면 가보는걸 추천 헬싱키가 넓진 않아서 여유있으실거에요

name: Design Museum
review_text: Mycket mindre än förväntat tyvärr, men finns en källare med en mindre utställning också + att arkitekturmuseet ingick, dock fanns det inte mycket mer än foton där.

name: Design Museum
review_text: Hieno parsinta

name: Design Museum
review_text: Место хорошее, но есть некоторые минусы , выбор что посмотреть есть, но расстраивает когда вместо вещи, лежит её фотография, это же всё таки музей, хочется чтобы было больше реальных вещей!? Так же я специально наблюдал за этим и за 20 минут, это случилось 3 раза учитывая то что почитателей было немного. Так вот о чём я, стенды выполнены в стиле вагонов поезда, и это выглядит интересно, в нутри этих вагонов хорошо освещённые предметы, они будто везут их во времени, наверное в этом задумка, но везут они эти предметы по деревянным палкам, и в главном зале справа от лестницы есть три вагона которые соединены одной доской, но расстояние между ними такое что можно обойти каждый вагон со всех сторон. И получается что ты смотришь внутрь вагона, хочешь обойти его и спотыкается об рельсину которую по хорошему можно и укоротить без какого либо урона.

name: Design Museum
review_text: סביר. לא מעבר לזה.

name: Design Museum
review_text: Отличный музей, идеальное место, чтобы ознакомиться с историей финского (и не только) дизайна: от дизайна стула и интерьера гостиной до архитектурных концептов зданий. Подача всех экспонатов увлекательная, скучать не приходилось совсем. Также были интерактивные экспонаты, в том числе с использованием VR шлемов. Рекомендую к посещению!

name: Design Museum
review_text:
Relativamente pequeño pero muy interesante. Aparte de exposiciones de larga duración tienen una zona permanente sobre la historia del diseño finlandés, actividades todo el año, cafetería y tienda. Visitas guiadas en inglés gratuitas.
Muy recomendable si pasas por Helsinki.

name: Design Museum
review_text:
Ich liebe formschöne, bunte und praktische Gegenstände. Hiervon gibt es im Designmuseum allerlei. Allerdings findet man m.E. zu wenig typisch finnische Designs. Ich hatte mir diesbezüglich mehr erwartet.
Und der stolze Eintrittspreis von 12 € für ein Museum, das auf allen drei Etagen  in einer Stunde besichtigt ist, tut sein Übriges. Da sollte der Träger des Museums noch ordentlich nachbessern. Weniger Eintritt, mehr (finnische) Exponate wäre die Devise.
